The paper involves the use of reinforcement learning algorithms to generate interactive content, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of actor-critic algorithms for policy learning and the generator network for environment creation suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on generating game levels and environments suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of graphics (cs.GR). The use of a generator network for environment creation may also suggest that the paper falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper's focus on procedural content generation suggests that it may also fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SD).
